{"lemma":"عَصاِ","slug":"عَصاِ","root":"ع.ص.#","root_slug":"ع-ص-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ص-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَصاِ","root":"عصو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":37},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":13},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29391"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B5%D8%A7%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"staff, stick"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"walking cane"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"punishment, chastisement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wooden handle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"scepter"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"crosier"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dominion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"penis"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lingual bone, tongue"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Muslim fraternity or a community in general"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to beat or strike with a stick, sword, or staff; to use, handle, wield, equip any of the above."},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dress wound, to use a splint on a wound"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to unite people for a purpose, to shepherd people together"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ʕiṣ́-. Cognate with Hebrew עֵץ (ʿēṣ)."},"ipa":["/ʕa.sˤan/","/ʕa.sˤaː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29391","headword_ar":"عَصًا","root":"ESw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwdN","text_ar":"عُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A staff,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rod"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSawN","text_ar":"عَصَوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and accordingly its dual is as below: said to be thus called because the fingers and hand are put together upon it [to grasp it], from the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSawotu Alqawoma","text_ar":"عَصَوْتُ القَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ I collected together the people, or party; ” as related by As from some one or more of the Basrees: (TA:) of the fem. gender: (S, Msb, K:) it is said in a prov., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaSaA mina AlEuSay~api","text_ar":"العَصَا مِنَ العُصَيَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The staff is from the little staff;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the dim. having the affix"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is the dim. of a fem. n.]; (S;) [or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaSaA","text_ar":"العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this prov. is the name of a mare of Jedheemeh [mentioned voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dul~N","text_ar":"ضُلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuSay~ap","text_ar":"العُصَيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is that of her dam; meaning that part of the thing, or affair, is from part; (S, K, TA;) and said when one is likened to his father; or meaning that the big thing is in its commencement small: (TA: [see also Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 17:]) it is not allowable to say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaA='","text_ar":"عَصَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"; nor to affix"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, TA:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi EaSaAYa A^atawak~aA^u EalayohaA","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ عَصَاىَ اَتَوَكَّاُ عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is my staff; I support,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stay, myself upon it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: Fr says that the first incorrect speech heard in El-'Irák was the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi EaSaAtiY","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ عَصَاتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) the dual is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSawaAni","text_ar":"عَصَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) and the pl. [of mult.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSiY~N","text_ar":"عُصِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSuwwN","text_ar":"عُصُووٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEuwlN","text_ar":"فُعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSiY~N","text_ar":"عِصِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is with kesr because of the kesrah following it, and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoSK","text_ar":"اَعْصٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoSaA='N","text_ar":"اَعْصَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or this last is agreeable with analogy, but has not been transmitted, (ISk, Msb,) and is disallowed by Sb, who says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuiSiY~N","text_ar":"عُِصِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"was used in its stead. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence various sayings, here following. ―         -b3- ]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloqaY EaSaAhu","text_ar":"اَلْقَى عَصَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threw down his staff;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he stayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rested,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceased from journeys,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having reached his place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) a prov.; (S, TA;) applied to him to whom an affair has become suitable and who has therefore kept to it: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made firm his tent-pegs, and pitched his tent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stayed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) like him who has returned from his journey. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaEa EaSaAhu","text_ar":"رَفَعَ عَصَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took up his staff"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he ceased from staying"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a place at which he had alighted; he departed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har p. 454.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tarofaEo EaSaAka Eano A^aholika","text_ar":"لَا تَرْفَعْ عَصَاكَ عَنْ اَهْلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Put not thou away thy staff,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick, from thy family,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy wife,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] denotes [the practice of] discipline. (S. [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rfE","text_ar":"رفع"},{"kind":"text","text":", p. 1122, col. 3.]) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo Eabiydu","text_ar":"هُمْ عَبِيدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaSaA","text_ar":"العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are the slaves of the staff"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they are"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persons"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beaten with the staff."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) It is said in the A,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsu Eabiydu AlEaSaA","text_ar":"النَّاسُ عَبِيدُ العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mankind are the slaves of the staff"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning that they are dreaded by reason of their doing harm [and are therefore to be kept in awe]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA humo A_il~aA Eabiydu AlEaSaA","text_ar":"مَا هُمْ اـِلَّا عَبِيدُ العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are none other than the slaves of the staff"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said of persons regarded as low, base, or vile. (TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lay~inu AlEaSaA","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَيِّنُ العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is one whose staff is supple"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is gentle, a good manager of that whereof he has the charge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K: *) accord. to ISd, alluding to the beating little with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ESA","text_ar":"عصا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu DaEiyfu AlEaSaA","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ ضَعِيفُ العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is one whose staff is weak"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiroEiy~apN","text_ar":"تِرْعِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who performs well the act of keeping"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tending,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of pasturing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feeding, camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who beats the camels little"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSA","text_ar":"عَصا"},{"kind":"text","text":": and such is commended. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saliybu","text_ar":"صَلِيبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaSaA","text_ar":"العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SulobuhaA","text_ar":"صُلْبُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One whose staff is hard"},{"kind":"text","text":"], i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who is ungentle with the camels, beating them with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ESA","text_ar":"عصا"},{"kind":"text","text":": and such is discommended. (TA.) See an ex. in a verse of Er-Rá'ee cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SulobN","text_ar":"صُلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraEahu biEaSaA AlmalaAmapi","text_ar":"قَرَعَهُ بِعَصَا المَلَامَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck him with the staff of censure"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he exceeded the usual bounds in censuring him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b9-  See also 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrE","text_ar":"قرع"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yuSal~iY EaSaA fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يُصَلِّى عَصَا فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one straightens the staff of such a one by turning it round over the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one manages, orders,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regulates, the affairs of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tadoxulo bayona AlEaSaA waliHaAy^ihaA","text_ar":"لَا تَدْخُلْ بَيْنَ العَصَا وَلِحَايِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Enter not thou between the staff and its peel"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intermeddle not thou between two close friends;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 153;) or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enter not thou into that which does not concern thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qa$arotu lahu AlEaSaA","text_ar":"قَشَرْتُ لَهُ العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I peeled for him the staff"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I discovered to him what was in my mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~u AlEaSaA","text_ar":"شَقُّ العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The splitting of the staff"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the contravening of the collective body"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the community"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of El-Islám"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Muslims"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) and also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the disuniting of the collective body of the tribe:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~a AlEaSaA","text_ar":"شَقَّ العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He separated himself from,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he contravened, the collective body"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the community"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) and [it is said that] the primary signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaSaA","text_ar":"العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the state of combination and union:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) this is the meaning in the saying, respecting the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xawaArij","text_ar":"خَوَارِج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xArijiY~N","text_ar":"خارِجِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado $aq~uwA EaSaA Almusolimiyna","text_ar":"قَدْ شَقُّوا عَصَا المُسْلِمِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They have made a schism in the state of combination and union,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the communion, of the Muslims"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) [Hence,] their saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iy~aAka waqatola AlEaSaA","text_ar":"اـِيَّاكَ وَقَتْلَ العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beware thou of slaying"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being slain in making a schism in the communion of the Muslims"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY $aq~i EaSaA Almusolimiyna","text_ar":"فِى شَقِّ عَصَا المُسْلِمِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aino$aq~ati AlEaSaA","text_ar":"اِنْشَقَّتِ العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The staff became split"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disagreement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discord, befell."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaArato EaSaA baniY fulaAnK $iqaqFA","text_ar":"طَارَتْ عَصَا بَنِى فُلَانٍ شِقَقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The staff of the sons of such a one flew in splinters"},{"kind":"text","text":"], a prov., meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sons of such a one became scattered in various directions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Meyd.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaA AlEabodi","text_ar":"عَصَا العَبْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The stick of the slave"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thing with which one stirs the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mal~ap","text_ar":"مَلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hot ashes wherein bread is baked"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaSaA","text_ar":"العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bone of the shank;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ESA","text_ar":"عصا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly so called]. (TA.) And [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEiSiY~u","text_ar":"العِصِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bones that are in the wing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And [the same, or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuSiY~u","text_ar":"العُصِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain stars, having the form of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaA","text_ar":"عَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ESY~","text_ar":"عصىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA. [But what stars these are, I have not been able to determine.]) ―         -b15-  Also, (i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaSaA","text_ar":"العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tongue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [Perhaps as being likened to a staff because used in chiding.] ―         -b16-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman's"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"muffler,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"headcovering, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximaAr","text_ar":"خِمَار"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b17-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaA Alr~aAEiY","text_ar":"عَصَا الرَّاعِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pastor's rod;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knot-grass; a species of polygonum, p. aviculare;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bTbAT","text_ar":"بطباط"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2069},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTobaAT","text_ar":"بَطْبَاط"},{"kind":"text","text":", but the former name is the better known];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male, and female, the former of which is the more potent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"asserted by Dioscorides to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diuretic, and a remedy for him who suffers suppression of the urine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Seenà, whom we call Avicenna, book ii. p. 229.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Msb","As","ISk"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}